        {
            "type": "h1-lesson",
            "content": "&#128218; &nbsp;The Präsens tense"
        },
        {
            "type": "h2-post",
            "content": "Introduction"
        },
        {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": "<p>The <b><i>Präsens</i></b> tense in German direclty corresponds to the present tense in English. It is used to describe actions that are happening right now or habitual actions. </br>However, it can also be used to describe future actions or actions happenning now with continuation on the future. This is because in German the future tense is rarely used and there is no present continuous. The <i>Präsens</i> should be the first tense to learn when starting to learn German.</p>"
        },
        {
            "type": "callout",
            "content": "<p>With the <i>Präsens</i>, you are getting 4 tenses in one: <strong>present</strong>, <strong>present continuous</strong>, <strong>present perfect</strong> and, in some cases, also the <strong>future</strong>! &nbsp;&nbsp; &#127881</p>"
        },
        {
            "type": "h2",
            "content": "Usage"
        },
        {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": "<p>We use the <i>Präsens</i> tense to express:</p>"
        },
        {
            "type": "list",
            "content": "heyy",
            "itemsList": {
                "items": [
                    {
                        "text": "<b>Present Actions:</b> Describing actions happening in the present.",
                        "example": {
                            "intro": "Example:",
                            "text": "Ich <a href='replace-url/verbs/lesen' target='_blank'>lese</a> ein Buch.",
                            "translation": "(I am reading a book.)"
                        }
                    },
                    {
                        "text": "<b>Habitual Actions:</b> Expressing routine or habitual actions.",
                        "example": {
                            "intro": "Example:",
                            "text": "Ich <a href='replace-url/verbs/trinken' target='_blank'>trinke</a> jeden Morgen Kaffee.",
                            "translation": "(I drink coffee every morning.)"
                        }
                    },
                    {
                        "text": "<b>General Truths:</b> Stating facts or general truths.",
                        "example": {
                            "intro": "Example:",
                            "text": "Die Erde <a href='replace-url/verbs/sind' target='_blank'> ist</a>rund.",
                            "translation": "(The Earth ist round.)"
                        }
                    },
                    {
                        "text": "<b>Actions already started and still happening:</b> In english we would use the present perfect tense: 'He has been playing...'.",
                        "example": {
                            "intro": "Example:",
                            "text": "Er <a href='replace-url/verbs/arbeiten' target='_blank'>arbeitet</a> seit 3 monate ins Kino.",
                            "translation": "(He has been working in the cinema for 3 months.)"
                        }
                    }
                ]
            }
        },{
            "type": "h2",
            "content": "Conjugation"
        },{
            "type": "h3",
            "content": "Regular verbs"
        },{
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": "<p>For regular verbs ending in <b data-verb-prefix>-en<\/b> (e.g., <a href='replace-url\/verbs\/splielen' target=\"_blank\">spiel<b data-verb-prefix>en<\/b><\/a> - <i>to play<\/i>), the infinitive ending <b data-verb-prefix>-en<\/b> is replaced by the following endings:<\/p>"
        },{
            "type": "table",
            "table": {
                "headings":  ["person", "ending", "example"],
                "rows": [
                    ["ich", "-e", "spiel<i>-e</i>"],
                    ["du", "-st", "spiel<i>-st</i>"],
                    ["es", "-t", "spiel<i>-t</i>"],
                    ["wir", "-en", "spiel<i>-en</i>"],
                    ["ihr", "-t", "spiel<i>-t</i>"],
                    ["Sie", "-en", "spiel<i>-en</i>"]
                ]
            }
        },{
            "type": "exercise-btn",
            "content": "practise präsens for splielen"
        },{
            "type": "h3",
            "content": "Irregular verbs"
        },{
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": "<p>Some irregular verbs require memorization since they will not follow any pattern (e.g., <a href='replace-url\/verbs\/sein' target=\"_blank\">sein<\/a> - <i>to play<\/i>):<\/p>"
        },{
            "type": "table",
            "table": {
                "headings":  ["person", "example"],
                "rows": [
                    ["ich", "<i>bin</i>"],
                    ["du", "<i>bist</i>"],
                    ["es", "<i>ist</i>"],
                    ["wir", "<i>sind</i>"],
                    ["ihr", "<i>seid</i>"],
                    ["Sie", "<i>sind</i>"]
                ]
            }
        },{
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": "<p>The 5 most important verbs of this type are the following: <a href='replace-url\/verbs\/sein' target=\"_blank\">sein<\/a>, <a href='replace-url\/verbs\/haben' target=\"_blank\">haben<\/a>, <a href='replace-url\/verbs\/werden' target=\"_blank\">werden<\/a>, <a href='replace-url\/verbs\/könen' target=\"_blank\">könen<\/a>, <a href='replace-url\/verbs\/mögen' target=\"_blank\">mögen<\/a></p>"
        },{
            "type": "h3",
            "content": "Stem-vowel changing irregular verbs"
        },{
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": "<p>Most of irregular verbs will only be stem-vowel changing, where the vowel in the stem changes in the <b>second and third person singular</b> (du and er/sie/es forms). There are three basic types of vowel change:</p>"
        },{
            "type": "list",
            "itemsList": {
                "items": [
                    {
                        "text": "<b>e  →  i:</b> for example <a href='replace-url\/verbs\/helfen' target=\"_blank\">helfen<\/a> (to read) changes the stem from <b data-verb-stem>\"e\"<\/b> to <b data-verb-stem>\"ie\"<\/b>:"
                    }
                ]
            }
        },{
            "type": "table-2-3",
            "table": {
                "headings":  ["person", "stem-change", "example"],
                "rows": [
                    ["ich", "", "helf<i>en</i>"],
                    ["du", "<b data-verb-stem>e  →  i<\/b>", "h<u>i</u>lf<i>st</i>"],
                    ["es", "<b data-verb-stem>e  →  i<\/b>", "h<u>i</u>lf<i>t</i>"],
                    ["wir", "", "helf<i>en</i>"],
                    ["ihr", "", "helf<i>t</i>"],
                    ["Sie", "", "helf<i>en</i>"]
                ]
            }
        },{
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": "<p>Other examples are <a href='replace-url\/verbs\/geben' target=\"_blank\">geben<\/a>, <a href='replace-url\/verbs\/sprechen' target=\"_blank\">sprechen<\/a> and <a href='replace-url\/verbs\/nehmen' target=\"_blank\">nehmen<\/a></p>"
        },{
            "type": "list",
            "itemsList": {
                "items": [
                    {
                        "text": "<b>e  →  ie:</b> for example <a href='replace-url\/verbs\/sehen' target=\"_blank\">sehen<\/a> (to read) changes the stem from <b data-verb-stem>\"e\"<\/b> to <b data-verb-stem>\"i\"<\/b>:"
                    }
                ]
            }
        },{
            "type": "table-2-3",
            "table": {
                "headings":  ["person", "stem-change", "example"],
                "rows": [
                    ["ich", "", "seh<i>e</i>"],
                    ["du", "<b data-verb-stem>e  →  ie<\/b>", "s<u>ie</u>h<i>st</i>"],
                    ["es", "<b data-verb-stem>e  →  ie<\/b>", "s<u>ie</u>h<i>t</i>"],
                    ["wir", "", "seh<i>en</i>"],
                    ["ihr", "", "seh<i>t</i>"],
                    ["Sie", "", "seh<i>en</i>"]
                ]
            }
        },{
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": "<p>Other examples are <a href='replace-url\/verbs\/lesen' target=\"_blank\">lesen<\/a>, <a href='replace-url\/verbs\/sehen' target=\"_blank\">sehen<\/a> and <a href='replace-url\/verbs\/stehlen' target=\"_blank\">stehlen<\/a></p>"
        },{
            "type": "list",
            "itemsList": {
                "items": [
                    {
                        "text": "<b>a  →  ä:</b> for example <a href='replace-url\/verbs\/fallen' target=\"_blank\">fallen<\/a> (to fall) changes the stem from <b data-verb-stem>\"a\"<\/b> to <b data-verb-stem>\"ä\"<\/b>:"
                    }
                ]
            }
        },{
            "type": "table-2-3",
            "table": {
                "headings":  ["person", "stem-change", "example"],
                "rows": [
                    ["ich", "", "fall<i>e</i>"],
                    ["du", "<b data-verb-stem>a  →  ä<\/b>", "f<u>ä</u>ll<i>st</i>"],
                    ["es", "<b data-verb-stem>a  →  ä<\/b>", "f<u>ä</u>ll<i>t</i>"],
                    ["wir", "", "fall<i>en</i>"],
                    ["ihr", "", "fall<i>t</i>"],
                    ["Sie", "", "fall<i>en</i>"]
                ]
            }
        },{
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": "<p>Other examples are <a href='replace-url\/verbs\/schlafen' target=\"_blank\">schlafen<\/a>, <a href='replace-url\/verbs\/fahren' target=\"_blank\">fahren<\/a> and <a href='replace-url\/verbs\/raten' target=\"_blank\">raten<\/a></p>"
        },{
